<h1 class="page-header">Test Emails with LetterOpener</h1>
<blockquote>
  <p>Preview email in the browser instead of sending it. This means you do not need to set up email delivery in your development environment, and you no longer need to worry about accidentally sending a test email to someone else's address.</p>
</blockquote>

<h3>Step 1</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>Add <code>letter_opener</code> to your Gemfile in <code>development</code> group</p>
  <pre><code>gem 'letter_opener'</code></pre>
</blockquote>

<h3>Step 2</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>Run Bundler</p>
  <pre><code>bundle</code></pre>
</blockquote>

<h3>Step 3</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>Configure your development environment to send emails with <code>letter_opener</code></p>
  <pre><code>config.action_mailer.delivery_method = :letter_opener</code></pre>
</blockquote>

<h3>Step 4</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>Send an email and look at the result from your browser</p>
</blockquote>

<h3>Step 5</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>Configure your views for a better output using <code>@subject</code> and <code>@comment</code></p>
  <p>HTML View</p>
  <pre><code>&lt;h3&gt;&lt;%= @subject %&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;%= @comment.text %&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</code></pre>
  <p>Text View</p>
  <pre><code>&lt;%= @subject %&gt;

&lt;%= @comment.text %&gt;</code></pre>
</blockquote>